But Big Creek, let's see, I believe in 1922, they 
moved a little steam rig in there, which, of

11:46.148 --> 12:03.967
course, at that time, this was a pretty good-sized 
drilling rig. But they drilled a well there on top

12:04.607 --> 12:14.738
of the dome, made a well that was 650 feet.

12:16.000 --> 12:23.749
It never was a whole lot of producer, but then they 
had to have oil to fire boil it with. And it amounted

12:25.712 --> 12:27.654
to a good bit. They pumped it there for a long time, 
the gasoline

12:27.674 --> 12:37.947
engine. There. Oh, they just jumped here and there 
and young of them. They make a well of caged linen,

