20:41.963 --> 20:45.949
after, because for a little while, it was hard to 
get materials. But as soon as things became

20:45.990 --> 20:49.495
available, yes, it began to grow. So I guess that 
covers everything. You have anything else to say

20:59.772 --> 21:02.917
or think of? Well, we've seen lots of changes. 
paved streets when they used to be so muddy, you'd

21:09.233 --> 21:23.268
get bogged down in Rosenberg, so sandy you'd get 
stuck in the sand over here in Spots, and air

21:09.233 --> 21:23.268
conditioning and all these things, and better 
cars. We've seen a lot of things change. When they

21:25.310 --> 21:37.063
got natural gas in here, they got running water, 
hot water, and you see Richmond

21:39.608 --> 21:49.819
Talk about these streets, Richmond sitting on 
Sandy, this main part of town, where there's

21:39.608 --> 21:49.819
nothing but sand. And the streets, when it was dry, 
when the sand blew and the buggy wheels kind of

21:52.142 --> 22:03.675
bogged up in that sand, So they went down on the 
river and dug up a bunch of clay and all, and then put

22:05.866 --> 22:13.873
clay on the streets to get out of the sand. Well, 
then when it rained, it got snow and muddy. So then

22:19.498 --> 22:32.089
they bought gravel and had it shipped in here and 
graveled the streets with big old rocks, a lot of

22:19.498 --> 22:32.089
it, like this. And then they'd get graveled up over 
in Colorado County. And finally, then, to get away

22:36.815 --> 22:43.863
from the rocks were the blacktop streets. That's 
where we are now. We have a very active library here

22:45.705 --> 22:51.832
now, a museum, I mean. And that little house 
between the bridges down here, you know, your east

22:52.613 --> 22:58.080
and westbound bridges? Yes, ma'am. The 
handworks? That little antique shop? Well, it's

